description: The tourist site in Datong city of Shanxi Province is known for its 252 caves and 51,000 Buddha statues. The administration is under heavy fire after a video showed timers installed outside the cubicles in the restroom. The timer shows the duration of the time the door had been shut. A staff member of the site said the installation of new timers was to "cope with an increase in the number of visitors for its innovative restroom management."
title: Top China tourist spot installs timers in women’s restrooms

description: Afghanistan's victory against Papua New Guinea in the T20 World Cup showcased their dark horse status, led by Fazalhaq Farooqi's impressive wicket-taking performance. This result eliminates New Zealand, who still have two group matches left, and guarantees Afghanistan's spot in the next round together with that of the hosts, the West Indies.
title: T20 WC: Afghanistan beat PNG to advance to Super Eights

description: Pakistan's T20 World Cup journey has been marred by back-to-back losses against the United States and India in the group stage. Despite bouncing back with a victory over Canada, the 2009 champions find themselves in a precarious position, with their hopes of advancing to the 'Super 8s' hanging by a thread.
title: 'If you say don't body-shame Azam, then respect Babar too'

description: Tesla shareholders have voted to reinstate CEO Elon Musk's $44.9 billion pay package. This decision comes after a Delaware judge had previously invalidated the compensation earlier this year. Tesla has said that it would appeal the decision but requested that shareholders reapprove the package at the company's annual meeting in Austin, Texas.
title: Musk wins back his $44.9 billion Tesla pay package

description: Nigel Farage's Reform UK has surpassed Prime Minister Rishi Sunak's Conservatives in a YouGov poll, showing Reform at 19% and the Conservatives at 18%. Despite this rise, Reform is not expected to gain many seats. Farage's return to frontline politics and leadership is boosting the party's popularity ahead of the July 4 election.
title: Opinion poll puts Reform UK ahead of Rishi Sunak's party

description: In the first video, he was seen awkwardly saluting Italy's Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni after he arrived for the G7 summit on Thursday. Social media users swiftly shared videos of the awkward salutation, which went viral. While some considered Biden's move out of touch, others applauded him for showing his Italian counterpart some dignity. Meloni, however, seemed unperturbed by the gesture and continued with her engagements.
title: Watch: Biden salutes Meloni, 'wanders off' at G7 summit

description: One of India's greatest batsmen Virender Sehwag needs no introduction; but Bangladesh captain Shakib Al Hasan made an impression, possibly sarcastically because of his latest criticism by Sehwag, that he didn't exactly identify who the journalist mentioned in his question.
title: 'Who?' Shakib intervenes a question on criticism by Sehwag

description: Sonakshi Sinha had spoken about the kind of bride she wants to be when she gets married, when the actress had once sported a bridal look for the ramp! She had said that she wants to be able to dance and have fun at her own wedding!
title: Watch: Sonakshi Sinha wants to be simplest bride ever on her wedding
Zelenskyy says Xi told him he will not sell weapons to Russia

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi touched down in Apulia, Italy on Thursday night to attend the G7 Summit. The ministry of external affairs said that PM Modi has a busy agenda, with several bilateral meetings and an outreach session planned for today. Upon his arrival at Brindisi Airport, PM Modi was received by India's Ambassador to Italy, Vani Rao, along with other officials.
title: PM Modi in Italy for G7 summit: What's on his agenda

description: RSS leader Indresh Kumar criticizes BJP for 'arrogance' and INDIA bloc for being 'anti-Ram' after Lok Sabha polls at Ramrath Ayodhya Yatra event near Jaipur.
title: 'Those who became arrogant were stopped at 241 by Lord Ram'

description: Darshan, a Sandalwood star, was arrested in Karnataka. The arrest raised questions in political and police circles about the involvement of key individuals, including Darshan's girlfriend Pavithra Gowda, in a murder case.
title: How engineer-turned-cop checkmated reel hero, jailed top Kannada film star Darshan

description: In Mangan district, landslides caused by heavy rain in north Sikkim led to casualties. The Teesta river overflowed, affecting NH-10 transportation routes.
title: 1,500 stranded, 6 dead in Sikkim, rain triggers floods in Kalimpong

description: Saurabh Netravalkar's inspirational journey in cricket receives praise from Suryakumar Yadav, Paras Mhambrey, and prepares for a crucial match against Ireland. The left-arm pace bowler was the talking point of the T20 World Cup after his match-winning Super Over against Pakistan. Now, just to prove he is no flash in the pan, Netravalkar has followed up that performance with the wickets of Kohli and "old mate" Rohit Sharma.
title: Emotional moment for me to get Virat's wicket: Netravalkar

description: Japan passed a law to prevent Apple and Google from restricting app sales, promoting competition. JFTC approved the law in April 2024, aiming to foster innovation and diverse services choice, emphasizing software security for smartphones.
title: Japan passes law to check Apple, Google's app dominance: What tech giants said

description: Indian cricket fans in New York witnessed a mix of victories and challenges, with Virat Kohli's struggles as an opener standing out. As the team heads to Miami for their final league game, Kohli's form remains a concern. Low scores of 1, 4 and 0 in three consecutive games isn't something that we have seen too often from the modern master, who came into the World Cup on the back of some magnificent knocks in the IPL.
title: T20 World Cup: A Virat-sized problem for Team India
